        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"contents\": [{\n    \"parts\":[\n      {\"text\": \"Determine whether the perspective is correct yes/no. Projection: Strict orthographic isometric projection. What it means: There is a complete lack of realistic perspective. All parallel lines on the object remain parallel in the image; they never converge to a single point on the horizon. Command: DO NOT use perspective view or a camera with two vanishing points. Camera height: shooting from a high angle. What this means: (~35-45° from the horizontal plane), with a tilt of ~30° in X (for “tilt”) and ~40° in Y (vertical descent). Visual marker: We should be able to see a significant portion of the tree canopy. Command: Simulate the view as if we were looking at an architectural model or object in a strategy game. Do NOT shoot from eye level. Angle of rotation: Classic game angle. What this means: The object is rotated so that its notional front is facing the viewer. Visual Marker: The vertical lines of the barrel remain perfectly vertical. Distortion-free: What this means: All proportions are preserved. The object in the background does not become smaller. The vertical parts do not tilt.\"},\n      {\n        \"inline_data\": {\n          \"mime_type\": \"image/jpeg\",\n          \"data\": \"{{ $json.data }}\"\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }]\n}\n",
